detailedDescription.articleBody: Fort Lauderdale is a city in the U.S. state of Florida, 25 miles north of Miami. It is the county seat of Broward County. As of the 2019 census, the city has an estimated population of 182,437.

detailedDescription.articleBody: The Iliad is an ancient Greek epic poem in dactylic hexameter, traditionally attributed to Homer. Set during the Trojan War, the ten-year siege of the city of Troy by a coalition of Greek states, it tells of the battles and events during the weeks of a quarrel between King Agamemnon and the warrior Achilles.
